Class AbstractTableViewModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • tableView.AbstractTableViewModel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, TableViewModel
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DefaultTableViewModel

    public abstract class AbstractTableViewModel
extends java.lang.Object
implements TableViewModel, java.io.Serializable
    This abstract class provides default implementations for most of the methods in the TableViewModel interface.

      • fireTableDataChanged

        protected void fireTableDataChanged()
        Notifies all listeners that all cell values in the table's rows may have changed. The number of rows may also have changed and the JTable should redraw the table from scratch. The structure of the table (as in the order of the columns) is assumed to be the same.
        See Also:
        TableModelEvent, EventListenerList
